annotation.TEXT: So, yeah. Since I played almost the whole game with the 3D effects off, I wasn't aware that that opening was more visible with them on. So, thanks for letting me know, SuperSupermario24.
Well, as you can see, a change has made regarding that. There is now a one-way tile here, which will prevent a player from getting him/herself trapped. Allow me to demonstrate.
What, really? The combo broke there?
Oh, you can indeed see the hole better in 3D mode.
And, whoops! I accidentally clicked outside the window there, which caused the game to automatically pause. Be careful of that if you're not playing in full screen.
...Yep. You can shortcut this way. You do miss out on the first gem by going this way, but this shortcut is really good to use in Time Attack mode.
Yep, it's a simple change, and doesn't alter the solution to the puzzle, but it fixes the potential trapping issue. Alright, now I'm done with this episode!
Once again, I'm leaving the enemy coins alone for the moment.
Bingo, the last gem is mine! Now... where could the exit possibly be? Hmm...
Whoa, man. Those cakes and that shooter enemy just dropped in. BTW, note that the shooter can destroy the cake blocks too. This'll eventually be important to know.
There was a health potion hiding within that cake, but I don't need it right now. Okay, now for more shooters.
Well, the voters have unanimously answered the question this time: 0 votes for 2-BOSS (not 2-B), and 6 votes for 2-B! So, 2-B it is!
...If I can aim right...
I almost forgot one other thing I meant to show in this episode! So, remember how I got myself trapped in the first gem's room in 2-8 last time?
Well, there's still this one stack of cakes left over here, so let's chow down! OMNOMNOM!!!
I guess I can grab this 10-value coin, since it's right there.
...Yeah, I'm not going back for any of the enemy coins, obviously. So, this level is done!
Ow, I took a couple of dumb hits there, and unfortunately, the health potion is unreachable now. At least Daria recovers a little bit of HP when she zaps enemies to death.
Hello, and welcome back to Miracle Fly! Now, before I get to the voting results, there's something that I want to show off that someone pointed out to me.
Triple combo! (3 kills, 3000 points)
Super combo! (4 kills, 5000 points)
I rested there to make sure I didn't run out of mana while over the floor spikes here, which would most likely be fatal.
Hyper combo! (5 kills, 7500 points)
I wonder if I can combo all of the remaining enemies together...
Let's begin by doing... this with the 1 walls.
Okay, what I want to show is in the area with the 2 walls. Specifically, the secret passage leading to the third gem.

Ah, and now the sign has changed to show that Daria has cleared it. Previously, once you cleared a level with a character, you couldn't change it. But, now you can, so you can't get screwed out of New Game+ anymore.
Wow, there's a lot of shooters here. Let's see how well I can combo them...
Oh, yeah. The little tutorial things always appear in this level every time you play it. At least they don't slow you down or impede your progress in any way.
When you're completely done with this portion of the level, hit the timer switch and go through the door. 12 seconds should be plenty of time to make it.

For some reason, the coins they drop aren't drawn to you when you get close either, so you gotta touch them directly. Anyway, to the left over there are some more coins, which I'll get to in a moment.
However, there's a good chance that I'll play both of those levels next time anyway, but your votes will determine what order I play them. So, vote for the one you want me to play first!
I didn't do that very well, but can I at least include the third shooter there in this combo?

!ush! ...Go, my red ! blocks, and fill the world with your redness! ...Wait, wrong game. Anyway, 20 seconds should be more than enough time to defeat these guys, especially if you ate the cakes above beforehand.
Alright, there's nothing special up above here, so let's just devour these cakes and move on.
Daria, you're up!
Super combo! (4 kills, 5000 points)
Anyway, I want Mira back on that sign, so I'm just quickly clearing the level again with her, at double footage speed.

Okay, now I'll go for them. I just wanted to include that enemy in that combo first. Also, that enemy dropped a coin too. In fact, every enemy in this level except for the ones behind the glass walls will drop a coin.
Alright, I'm done with this level! BTW, I did notice my coin amount, and if this level didn't require collecting all coins, I would've left one behind so that I could get the 3-star bonus.

Oh, man. These coins here are going up and down, periodically beyond the spikes. Be careful when trying to collect them, but it shouldn't be too hard. Oh, and like the dancing coins before, these aren't drawn to you if you get close.
To be continued... Yo!
Obviously, you want to carefully get past the spikes here, and don't let the moving spike blocks crush you against the floor or ceiling, or else... take a wild guess what happens.
Oh, man... Look at all those coins dancing over there. I think they're doing a square dance.
Oh, I see the exit portal! But, be careful not to hit it too soon if you want to get all the coins buried in these cakes.
Now, let's quickly complete the level with Daria.
Whoa, I almost hit the spikes up there. It wouldn't have been too big a deal, though, since there's that nearby health potion if I need it.
Alright, let's turn the 3D effects back off and get outta here.
Yep, as you can see, you can destroy the cakes by shooting them, and you'll gain 100 points per destroyed tile. Next, watch out for the bouncing spiked balls as you get the first gem.
Note that these coins aren't drawn to you when you get close to them like with most coins. You have to actually collect them directly. Watch out for the < shots, of course.

8031 is not bad at all, although I probably could've improved that by a few hundred if I had ignored that 10-coin early on, avoided hitting any bats, and not stumbled a bit with collecting the mana star.
Alright, that unlocked 3-8. So yeah, I can skip 2-BOSS and most of world 3 for now if I want.
Very good. Now, let's kill some more shooters...
And it broke there too. Well, that's a bummer. I didn't think I had rested on the ground for too long between kills there, but the game apparently thought otherwise.
Fortunately, 10 seconds is way more than enough time to get through both gates between the timer switch and the exit chamber.
Got 'em! That hit I took doesn't matter, since I'd already finished my combo by that point! Oh, and that last enemy was holding a gem!
Let's do 1-4, and I guess I'll go with Mira this time.
"Click."
Hmm... The action has slowed down a bit. This must be one of those levels that lags on me while the 3D effects are active.
Also, I guess I could crash into that one bat, since he was right there.
Of course, I want to collect them all, not just to satisfy my OCD or get the star for collecting all coins at the end. There's another reason, too...
So, let's go back into 2-9 here real quick...
And, there we go. The 1-1 sign shows Mira again.

Alright, and... would you look at that! The coins in those cakes brought me up to exactly 64, which is a valid number for the 3-star bonus. Now, the next such number would be 73, but I don't think I left 9 enemy coins behind, so...
Alright, so the voting candidates this time are: 3-9 (Sweet Land), and 2-BOSS (The King of Rabbit).
Unfortunately, it isn't always perfectly clear when the combo has broken, so if you've been making use of split-second landings, you might find yourself disappointed when you get your next kill.
Okay, now for that age-old question again: 2-B, or not 2-B?
Triple combo! (3 hits, 3000 points)
Now, I was told that you could more clearly see the secret passage while in 3D mode, so let's go to the options and turn on the 3D effects.
Up here is a gang of 3 shooters, and you'll definitely want to destroy them.
That unlocks 3-9, which sounds like a sweet level. Now, I don't think I'll have enough time for one more new level today, but I guess I could play another Time Attack level real quick.
To be-- Whoa, hold it!

Yeah, remember that Miracle Fly video I uploaded on my previous birthday? Yep, it was of this level, "Happy Cake Day". So, we get to see this place and all of its deliciously destructible cakes again!

Next, hit this yellow switch, and watch out for the falling spike balls. It shouldn't be difficult to get the gem above afterward. Then, try your best to avoid the spike balls as you get out of there.
And the reason is... they drop coins, even if you're not using Irvette. And, who doesn't want coins?
Triple combo! (3 kills, 3000 points)
Triple combo! (3 kills, 3000 points)
Yep, as that "click" sound indicated, the gate opened when I collected that final coin, so I can now get the last gem!
Hmm... In thinking about it, I should get the coins those shooters dropped right now, because I eventually will be unable to return down here.
Now, do you see that gate up there that's blocking the gem? That gate only opens if you collect every single coin in the level. So, that's why I've been making sure to get them all so far.
Yep! Okay, so what needs to be done next? Well, it looks like the blue switch must be hit in order to advance, but be ready when you do so.
There's some more tricky-looking coins here. Man, you sure have to go a bit out of your way for many of the coins in this level, but there's a reason for that, which will become apparent soon.
I'll leave that enemy coin there alone for the moment, since I don't think there'll be any more colored gate switches in this level, so I'll be able to come back for it later if I want.
Okay, now did I collect every coin in the level? Let's find out...
Mira would be a far better choice for comboing here. Anyway, make sure to pick up the coins they drop, as usual.
Okay, there's another thing I want to show, which involves a recent update to the game. For this, let's go back to 1-1 here, and note that the sign shows that I've cleared it with Mira.
There's a couple of shooters up here, including a really tiny one. Gun them down as usual. (Although, you're not required to like in 2-B, but it's still a good idea.)
Anyway, there's a red ! switch down there, but you definitely want to clear out the cakes up here first before hitting it, because guess where the enemies will appear!
I guess I will at least play 3-8 right now, and it's Irvette's turn. Now, you guys might remember this level from one of my earlier videos...
Okay, that's all of those tricky coins. BTW, if you're using Mira, you might be able to kill the shooters behind the glass walls, but those ones don't drop coins, so it's not vital to kill them.
